From 3c6dc4138a42138870b581e0c305d4871b57d9b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: a <a@b>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 08:58:39 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] igb 6.12-ethercat: add notified arg to igb_ndo_fdb_add
 (kernel 6.17)

Kernel 6.17 extended the ndo_fdb_add net-device op signature with a
'bool *notified' output parameter, placed before the existing extack
parameter:

  static int (*ndo_fdb_add)(struct ndmsg *ndm, struct nlattr *tb[],
                            struct net_device *dev,
                            const unsigned char *addr, u16 vid,
                            u16 flags,
                            bool *notified,
                            struct netlink_ext_ack *extack);

The new arg lets drivers signal to the bridge layer whether they have
already issued an RTM_NEWNEIGH notification for the operation, avoiding
duplicate notifications. The IgH-patched igb driver does not need this
behaviour (it never notifies internally), so the parameter is added to
the signature for ABI compatibility and otherwise unused.

On the etherlab.org/ethercat gitlab stable-1.6 base, the 'notified'
parameter was already present but guarded by '#ifdef CONFIG_SUSE_KERNEL'
because earlier kernels only had it in the SUSE backport. Kernel 6.17
landed the same arg in mainline, so the guard must be removed for the
arg to be visible on a stock kernel build.

Without this patch the kernel build fails with:
  error: initialization of 'int (*)(...)' from incompatible pointer type
  for the entry .ndo_fdb_add = igb_ndo_fdb_add
---
 devices/igb/igb_main-6.12-ethercat.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/devices/igb/igb_main-6.12-ethercat.c b/devices/igb/igb_main-6.12-ethercat.c
index c6bf418..d644e85 100644
--- a/devices/igb/igb_main-6.12-ethercat.c
+++ b/devices/igb/igb_main-6.12-ethercat.c
@@ -2513,9 +2513,7 @@ static int igb_ndo_fdb_add(struct ndmsg *ndm, struct nlattr *tb[],
 			   struct net_device *dev,
 			   const unsigned char *addr, u16 vid,
 			   u16 flags,
-#ifdef CONFIG_SUSE_KERNEL
 			   bool *notified,
-#endif
 			   struct netlink_ext_ack *extack)
 {
 	/* guarantee we can provide a unique filter for the unicast address */
-- 
